This directory contains the experiments used to generate learning curves data and plots

get log joint values:
    cat $1 | grep LogJoint | cut -d= -f4
pom.xml
    defines job dependencies. Do mvn clean dependency:copy-dependencies to get them all into target/dependency/*
submit.py
    Submits jobs to fsl and writes output to results/
aggregate.sh
    usage ./aggregate results > results.csv
    Takes a header from one file, and concatenates the body of each csv file in results into a single csv file
learningcurves.R
    Plots the resulting concatenate csv
ssh_submit.py
    Runs jobs on the potatos using the jobfarm.py script:
    ./ssh_submit.py -n potatos -o out -r results/tst --stage=2
    Dry run with simulated errors:
    ./ssh_submit.py --test -n potatos -o out -r results/tst --stage=2 -c

`mvn clean dependency:copy-dependencies; ./distribute.ssh potatos`
    copies all datasets and experiments to all potatos that jobs will be run on. do this prior to ssh_submit and after every time you change the maven artifacts referred to by the pom.xml

To generate simulated newsgroups results
# link multiann.py to multiann-newsgroups-simulation.py 
`rm multiann.py; ln -s multiann-newsgroups-simulation.py multiann.py`
`./ssh_submit.py -n potatos -o /tmp/out0820 -r /local/plf1/git/Experiments/plf1/TACL-2015-Measurements-submission/results/2015-08-20`
`./gather.sh potatos results/2015-08-20-newsgroupssim; ./cleanup.sh results/2015-08-20-newsgroupssim/; ./aggregate.sh results/2015-08-20-newsgroupssim > csv/2015-08-20-newsgroupssim.csv`

To generate the weather-preds results with real annotation order:
`rm multiann.py; ln -s multiann-weather-preds.py multiann.py`
`./ssh_submit.py  -n potatos -o /tmp/out0820-weatherreal -r /local/plf1/git/Experiments/plf1/TACL-2015-Measurements-submission/results/2015-08-20-weatherreal`
`./gather.sh potatos results/2015-08-20-weatherreal; ./cleanup.sh results/2015-08-20-weatherreal/; ./aggregate.sh results/2015-08-20-weatherreal > csv/2015-08-20-weatherreal.csv`

To generate the weather results using labeled location measurements:
`rm multiann.py; ln -s multiann-weather-loclabels.py multiann.py`
`./ssh_submit.py  -n potatos -o /tmp/out0820-weather-loclabels -r /local/plf1/git/Experiments/plf1/TACL-2015-Measurements-submission/results/2015-08-20-weather-loclabels`
`./gather.sh potatos results/2015-08-20-weather-loclabels; ./cleanup.sh results/2015-08-20-weather-loclabels/; ./aggregate.sh results/2015-08-20-weather-loclabels > csv/2015-08-20-weather-loclabels.csv`
